#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:1 f44c81cbd24d40458f064d285596b967
msgid ""
"Mapflow Imagery Search enables searching metadata for mosaic providers "
"(e.g., ArcGIS World Imagery, Global mosaic)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:4 9d1ecfb33c22498b981a650ab0eb1cbe
msgid ""
"**🌏 Global mosaic** is the annually updated satellite imagery composite "
"covering most of the World. The mosaic is composed of \"Jilin\" Chinese "
"satellites imagery (RGB, 0.75–0.5 m/px). The preview is limited to zoom "
"14. **🌏 ArcGIS World Imagery** is a provider of the global coverage "
"composed of high and medium resolution satellite imagery and aerial "
"imagery, hosted by ESRI. The frequency of updating images is 1-5 years "
"depending on the territory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:7 2b163a77d1514bd2a2dc24de8a5d87cc
msgid ""
"How to use :doc:`Mapflow – QGIS <qgis_plugin>` to search for mosaic's "
"metadata and run the analysis:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:9 31565d4a90ae412fa093ac4e644e9417
msgid "Switch to the Tab \"Imagery Search\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:10
#: 0625ce3eaecd41aa8007d4bc86a85425
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Set search filter parameters including the area (it can be your area of "
"analysis or a map canvas), period of time, cloud %, and the % of the "
"intersection with AOI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:11
#: 033e55ecb769415ea9ea307746095d1e
msgid ""
"Select the \"Product type = Mosaic\" in the Search results. You will see "
"the mosaic image \"cutline\" indicating the specific image that is used "
"in the mosaic."
msgstr ""

#: 9dfab2f258fa4ffb8fc2ba8b0d731880
msgid "Search for Mosaic images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:22
#: 0b5bf5a48c8545a6b41d96c2b6ca400a
msgid ""
"There are two types of products in the Imagery Search API available: * "
"The **Scene** product is available for ordering by request. Now you need "
"to contact us to order the specific image. * The **Mosaic** product is "
"available for instant analysis if the corresponding data provider is "
"linked to your Mapflow account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:26
#: 541260852f0c4f6499e9353796a243c4
msgid ""
"Run the processing. The resulting area of analysis will be clipped by the"
" intersection with the area of analysis."
msgstr ""

#: 7ecc578f0d6c4d78986958e363f3c878
msgid "Get results based on Mosaic analysis"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/search_mosaic.rst:35
#: 2fd547d09fc041fdb35aee91e26955d4
msgid ""
"To run the processing over the whole area of analysis – just clear the "
"selection and use the **Data Source: 🌏 Global mosaic 2022** or the **Data"
" Source: 🌏 ArcGIS World Imagery**."
msgstr ""

